12:
That didn't hurt... Not even a little!
H-heheh! I can take way worse than
that!
16:
Just because you can, doesn't
mean you should! You took the
brunt of that last hit, and it was
nothing to sneeze at.
20:
We should take a break here. Both of
us need to be in top shape if we're
going to beat those things.
27:
Where are we anyway? Some kinda
weird cave? Ruins? Weren't we just
fighting outside?
34:
Think we passed through that hole?
It looks so weird... Doesn't seem like
something a primal beast would've
made.
53: How kind of you to follow us over.
58:
Actually, this is our chance! Me and
Embrasque are charged up and
ready to go!
62:
Ahaha, that's the spirit. Guess it's
better than letting our prey get
away, huh?
71:
Heheh, leave this to us! Come on,
Embrasque!
77:
No monsters here either.
Something's gotta be off.
81:
The previous shift was different than
usual... Could the monsters have run
away in fear?
91: Are you all right?! What's going on?
99:
Sorry, but it's dangerous here. 
You need to leave—
109:
What are those creatures?! Careful,
Alk, those aren't normal monsters!
113:
That's right—they're primal beasts!
You guys need to get out while you
still can!
Bea, can you stand?
119:
Ha, course I can! Take much more
than that to put me outta
commission!
125:
We'll have to buy time until these
people can evacuate, Bea!
140:
What?! Nuh-uh, are you crazy!
They're PRIMAL BEASTS! We're not
kidding!
144:
I'm not sure what that even is... I just
know that I won't abandon someone
who could use a hand!
149:
Besides, nothing wrong with
strength in numbers when you're
fighting tough ones, yeah?
154:
Couple of good eggs, aren't you?
Reminds me of a certain someone
we know.
158:
Okay, then. We'll be counting on you,
but don't let yourselves get hurt!
162:
Might want to listen to her. Their hits
REALLY hurt!
166:
Time for some payback! Leave the
final blow to me!
